Sentencas: SSC (70 wt.% SrSc0.2Co0.8O3-delta) SDC (30 wt.% Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9) composite was evaluated as cathode for intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: A composite oxygen-reduction electrode composed of SrSc0.2Co0.8O3-δ perovskite and Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for an intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The effect of firing temperature on the chemical interaction between SSC and SDC was characterized by oxygen-temperature programmed desorption (O-2-TPD) techniques.
Titulo: A composite oxygen-reduction electrode composed of SrSc0.2Co0.8O3-δ perovskite and Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for an intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: Certain type of phase reactions occurred between SSC and SDC at calcination temperatures higher than 950 degrees C.
Titulo: A composite oxygen-reduction electrode composed of SrSc0.2Co0.8O3-δ perovskite and Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for an intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The conductivity of the composite was measured by a four-prober direct current technique.
Titulo: A composite oxygen-reduction electrode composed of SrSc0.2Co0.8O3-δ perovskite and Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for an intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The electro-catalytic activity of the composite electrode for oxygen reduction was measured by electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) in a symmetric cell configuration.
Titulo: A composite oxygen-reduction electrode composed of SrSc0.2Co0.8O3-δ perovskite and Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for an intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: The electrode fired at 950 degrees C showed the best performance.
Titulo: A composite oxygen-reduction electrode composed of SrSc0.2Co0.8O3-δ perovskite and Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for an intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: By applying the SSC + SDC-composite electrode, a cell with a similar to 20-mu m thick SDC electrolyte delivered a peak power density of 760 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: A composite oxygen-reduction electrode composed of SrSc0.2Co0.8O3-δ perovskite and Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 for an intermediate-temperature solid-oxide fuel cell
